{"id": 227489576, "title": "Straphanger shot and wounded on NYC subway as gunman remains at large", "text": "A man was shot and wounded on an uptown 4 train on the Upper East Side early Sunday, and the shooter is still at large. The 31-year-old victim was shot in his left hand while on the train at East 86th Street and Lexington Avenue around 2:30 a.m. Sunday, police told The Post. Cops said they do not have a suspect, and the shooter quickly fled the scene after opening fire. It was not immediately clear whether the victim and suspect knew each other. The victim was taken to Cornell Hospital by EMS in stable condition. His identity has not been released. The NYPD investigation is ongoing.", "summary": "The 31-year-old victim was shot in his left hand while on a the train train at East 86th Street and Lexington Avenue around 2:30 a.m. Sunday, police told The Post.", "url": "https://nypost.com/2024/06/02/us-news/man-shot-on-4-train-near-86th-street-gunman-at-large/", "image": "https://nypost.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/06/commuters-seen-union-sq-subway-19492531.jpg?quality=75&strip=all&w=1200", "video": "https://cdn.jwplayer.com/videos/9N8dR787-RyIcpnTz.mp4", "publish_date": "2024-06-02 12:08:19", "author": "Isabel Keane,Larry Celona", "authors": ["Isabel Keane", "Larry Celona"], "language": "en", "source_country": "us", "sentiment": -0.39}